TY1MTk3OTQyMiwiYXNzZXRfYWdlX2RheXMiOjQsInZpX3VzZWNhc2VfaWQiOjEwMDk5LCJkdXJhdGlvbl9zIjo1OSwidXJsZ2VuX3NvdXJjZSI6Ind3dyJ9&ccb=17-1&vs=87f8d0daa2aa52f2&_nc__JnyBxUCKAJDMywXQE3d0vGp--cYEmRhc2hfYmFzZWxpbmVfMV92MREAdf4HZeadAQA&_nc_gid=V4TCi8pIUUbpkHgdT7Xkhw&_nc_ss=72689&_nc_zt=28&oh=00_AQAOJyB8sDhPR5VuHarCUMcEZnbDGVFq_cDkHxkihYUImw&oe=6A5DAFDE", "musicInfo": {"artist_name": "the_organised_mum", "song_name": "Original audio", "uses_original_audio": true, "should_mute_audio": false, "should_mute_audio_reason": "", "audio_id": "37379677921623337"}, "ownerUsername": "the_organised_mum", "ownerFullName": "Gemma Bray Founder of TOM", "transcript": "Some, it's no surprise to you whatsoever that I love a routine. I don't have a routine, I can feel a little bit wibbly wobbly. I know that over the coming days some of you might be in the same boat, especially if you've got kids that are just about to break up for the summer. You might be thinking, hold on a minute, I've been looking forward to it, I've been looking forward to not having to do the school run. It might feel great when initially that routine relaxes, but there may come a point, not necessarily, but there may come a point where you're a bit more overwhelmed than you thought you were going to, and I'm going to tell you why. When you're doing the school run in the morning, you've got a hard deadline. You have got a framework imposed externally on you and you have not got a choice, which means that the decisions have kind of been taken out of your hands. When that school run doesn't exist for the summer, that framework doesn't exist either. All of a sudden you are having to make more decisions, and to an already overwhelmed brain, that doesn't feel great, and it can result in you feeling overloaded, a little bit snappy, not as relaxed as you thought you were going to do. Forewarned is forearmed. If you know that that wobble is coming, you're like, do you know what, this is entirely normal."}, {"shortCode": "Daupk_qNOKT", "